        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 7 at 12:16PM MDT by NWS Pocatello ID</headline>
        <description>At 1216 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fort Hall Bannock Creek Lodge, or 8 miles southwest of Pocatello,
moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pocatello, Chubbuck, Inkom, Portneuf Gap, Fort Hall Bannock Creek
Lodge, and Mink Creek Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
